@@JvXPSetDrawFlags
<TITLE JvXPSetDrawFlags procedure>
Summary
  Adjusts Flags according to the values of the parameters.
Description
  Use JvXPSetDrawFlags as an easy way to set Flags with the alignment and word wrap values. The
  DT_ENDELLIPSIS value is always included in Flags. Flags can be used in calls to DrawText and <LINK
  JvXPRenderText>.
Parameters
  AAlignment - The alignment to include in Flags
  AWordWrap  - The word wrap value to include in Flags.
  Flags      - Modified to include the values of AAlignment and AWordWrap.
See Also
  <DELPHILINK DrawText>, JvXPRenderText

