@@JvXPAdjustBoundRect
<TITLE JvXPAdjustBoundRect procedure>
Summary
  Adjust a TRect based on several parameters.
Description
  JvXPAdjustBoundRect is used to modify the size of a TRect based on the current value of several
  properties. When entering the procedure, Rect should be set to the current bounding rect of the
  control. When returning, Rect has been modified with the new values.
Parameters
  BorderWidth    - Width of the controls borders.
  ShowBoundLines - Determines if BoundLines is valid.
  BoundLines     - Contains a set of edges that are showing in the control.
  Rect           - At entry, contains the bounding rect of the control. At exit, contains the
  modified                   values.

